PART B (#2) -- BDS adequacy: raw FW returns vs FW GJR residuals
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  Asymptotic BDS statistic (m=2), mean +/- sd across paths
  [reference only -- asymptotic SEs unreliable under heavy tails]:
    raw FW returns      :    6.20 +/- 2.59
    FW GJR residuals    :   -0.19 +/- 1.03
    -> filtering removes ~97% of the raw BDS magnitude

  Bootstrap (permutation) BDS test [primary -- heavy-tail robust]:
    raw FW returns      : rejects iid in 92% of 60 paths  (median p=0.005)
    FW GJR residuals    : rejects iid in 3% of 60 paths  (median p=0.432)
  A high raw rejection rate collapsing to near the 5% nominal level on
  residuals = GJR captured the dependence (the raw 'nonlinearity' was
  volatility clustering). A residual rejection rate still well above 5%
  would indicate leftover structure GARCH missed. This bootstrap result,
  not the asymptotic statistic above, is the one to report.

